teaser: May 2, 2019 • Will Johnson is a successful producer and songwriter who found himself questioning the music industry and his place in it. So this time, he's trying a business approach from the world of fine art.
title: Can Musicians Avoid Commercial Pressure And Still Make A Living? WILLS Is Trying

teaser: May 1, 2019 • Smithsonian Folkways archivist and Pete Seeger expert Jeff Place talks about Pete Seeger: The Smithsonian Folkways Collection, due out on what would have been Seeger's 100th birthday.
title: Pete Seeger's Legacy Gets Immortalized With 'Smithsonian Folkways' Collection

teaser: May 1, 2019 • In Melbourne for its eighth iteration, the All-Star Global Concert brought together marquee names in jazz around a concert program of international, but borderless, collaboration.
title: Herbie Hancock Aims Jazz Day All-Star Concert Towards A World In 'Turmoil'

teaser: April 30, 2019 • Kelsey Lu knew she wanted to play music from a young age. So, at 18, she left home to deepen that study. On her debut album, Blood, Lu explores what that decision meant.
title: Kelsey Lu, A Classically Trained Rule Breaker

teaser: April 29, 2019 • The Dentsu Aegis Network, which had been funding the ambitious, three-day 50th-anniversary music festival with headliners including Jay-Z and Santana, says that the August event will not happen.
title: Woodstock 50 Canceled By Its Investors

teaser: April 29, 2019 • You may not recognize the Austrian composer by name, but if you like cartoons, you've heard the music of Franz von Suppé.
title: From Betty Boop To Popeye, Franz Von Suppé Survives In Cartoons

teaser: April 26, 2019 • Brothers Matt and Brad Shultz of Cage the Elephant have learned to lean on each other through a chaotic childhood and the recent losses in their lives.
title: Cage The Elephant Processes Grief With 'Social Cues'
